Package org.wmn4j.notation.elements

Contains classes and interfaces for the basic elements of music notation.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Durational
    Interface for all the notation objects that have a duration.
    Part
    Interface for parts in a score.
    Part.Iter
    Interface for Part Iterators.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Chord
    Class for chords.
    Clef
    Class for clefs.
    Clefs
    Common clefs.
    Duration
    The Duration class represents the duration of any musical object with a duration such as a note or a rest.
    Durations
    Collection of basic durations.
    KeySignature
    Class for key signatures.
    KeySignatures
    Collection of typical key signatures associated with major and minor keys.
    Measure
    Class that defines a measure.
    Measure.Iter
    Iterator for Durational objects in a Measure.
    MeasureAttributes
    Class containing the attributes of measures that typically remain unchanged from one measure to the next.
    MultiNoteArticulation
    Class that represents markings that span across multiple notes, such as slurs and glissando.
    MultiStaffPart
    Class for parts that have multiple staves such as keyboard instruments.
    MultiStaffPart.Iter
    Iterator for MultiStaffPart Iterates through the measures by going through all staves for a certain measure number before going on to the next measure.
    Note
    Class that defines a note.
    Pitch
    The Pitch class represents a pitch.
    Rest
    This class represents a rest.
    Score
    Class that describes a score.
    SingleStaffPart
    Class for representing a part consisting of a single staff in a score.
    SingleStaffPart.Iter
    Iterator for SingleStaffPart.
    Staff
    Class for representing a staff in a score.
    TimeSignature
    Class for time signatures.
    TimeSignatures
    Common time signatures.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Articulation
    Note specific articulations.
    Barline
    Barline types.
    Clef.Type  
    Key
    Major and minor keys.
    MultiNoteArticulation.Type
    The type of the articulation.
    Part.Attribute
    Attribute types that a Part can have.
    Pitch.Base
    The letter in a pitch name.
    PitchClass
    Represents the 12 pitch classes in equal-temperament tuning.
    Score.Attribute
    Type for the different text attributes a score can have.
    Staff.Type
    Type of staff.

Package org.wmn4j.notation.elements Description

Contains classes and interfaces for the basic elements of music notation.
